      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>To provide programs that increase the social, economic, educational, health-related and recreational opportunities to the residents of the Meramec region.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Delta Regional Authority Naturally Meramec Grant. The project consists of three basic components: 1) Small business education and training through "Good Agricultural Practices" Certification, commercial composting and food safety trainings. 2)Regional Marketing &amp; Promotion through website development, local food event promotion, establishing regional day/weekend trips, branding and social media. 3) Food Hub development</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>0</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>29139</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
      </ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>Missouri Department of Economic Development Grant for affordable connectivity program outreach. The Affordable Connectivity Program (ACP) is a US government program run by the Federal Communications Commission to help low-income households pay for internet service and connected devices like a laptop or tablet. The ACP Outreach Grant Program provides eligible governmental and non-governmental entities with the funding and resources needed to increase awareness of and participation in the ACP among those eligible households most in need of affordable connectivity. Program Service expenses include $25,702 contract services, $2,596 grant administration, match $707 and license fee $134</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
        <GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>0</GrantsAndAllocationsAmt>
        <ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>14030</ProgramServiceExpensesAmt>
