    <ReasonableCauseExplanation documentId="R000004" softwareId="22015720" softwareVersionNum="v1.00">
      <ExplanationTxt>Meramec Community Enhancement Corporation (MCEC) has a contract with Meramec Regional Planning Commission (MRPC) for staffing assistance, and it was a MRPC staff member who failed to carry out her responsibilities of filing the 990 EZs in a timely fashion and requesting extensions when necessary. This was during COVID when staff were trying to deal with the impact of COVID. This staff member was impacted by COVID and other medical issues and was also caring for ailing, elderly family members and a spouse with a terminal disease. Her husband passed away during this time. Staff were working remotely for a while and then hybrid, and it was very difficult to track work responsibilities when you are accustomed to working together, in-person in one building. Additionally, MRPC was understaffed, and staff were trying to do more to cover for that shortfall. Unfortunately, the staff member did not inform her manager that she was missing extension deadlines and requests, until we received the automatic revocation letter in July 2023. I believe the stress and pressure of COVID and the added family responsibilities greatly impacted job performance, and MCEC suffered from that situation. Staff applied for reinstatement and promptly mailed a hard copy of the completed 990EZ form after receiving the IRS reinstatement letter. However, the IRS returned the 990 filing because they required it be filed electronically. Staff had to research low or no-cost platforms to submit the filing. All of these things caused significant delays in filing for June 30, 2023. I believe we have a system in place to ensure future compliance, and management ensures timely filings moving forward.</ExplanationTxt>
    </ReasonableCauseExplanation>
